# Optional: Cloudflare Turnstile site key (must pair with API TURNSTILE_SECRET)
# When the player site and core API are on different origins, set the API base (no trailing slash).
# **Vercel / production:** you MUST set VITE_PLAYER_API_ORIGIN to your public Go API URL or login/register calls
# hit the static host and fail (HTTP 404 / "network"). Also add the player site URL to PLAYER_CORS_ORIGINS on core.
# Leave unset for local dev — Vite proxies /v1 and /health to DEV_API_PROXY (default http://127.0.0.1:9090).
# If the API runs on another port (e.g. PORT=9090 in services/core/.env), set:
# DEV_API_PROXY=http://127.0.0.1:9090
#
# Optional ISO2 stub for geo denial tests in local dev (Vite adds X-Geo-Country on proxied /v1 and /health only).
# DEV_GEO_COUNTRY=GB
#
# To hit a hosted API (e.g. Render) from local dev **without CORS issues**, use the Vite proxy:
#   DEV_API_PROXY=https://crypto-casino-1938.onrender.com
# (no trailing slash). Leave `VITE_PLAYER_API_ORIGIN` **unset** so the browser calls same-origin `/v1/...`
# and Vite forwards to Render (see vite.config.ts `server.proxy`).
# **CORS:** You do **not** need to edit `PLAYER_CORS_ORIGINS` on Render for this setup — the browser only calls
# same-origin `/v1` on the dev server; Vite proxies to the API. Keep your existing Vercel/production entries unchanged.
# (Only if you set `VITE_PLAYER_API_ORIGIN=https://…` to hit the API **directly** from the browser must you **append**
# `http://localhost:5174` to that same comma-separated list — never replace your Vercel hosts.)
# **Caveat:** You are exercising **production** data and flags (Oddin, games, limits). Safer for read-only checks;
# avoid destructive admin/player actions against prod unless intended.
# **Fingerprint (legacy):** live core defaults off (`REQUIRE_FINGERPRINT_PLAYER_AUTH` unset = false). If you explicitly
# turn it on in core, also set VITE_FINGERPRINT_ENABLED=1 + VITE_FINGERPRINT_PUBLIC_KEY + VITE_FINGERPRINT_REGION on the player.
# Otherwise use DEV_API_PROXY=http://127.0.0.1:9090 with local core so login is not blocked.
# Only use `VITE_PLAYER_API_ORIGIN=https://…` when you need direct browser→API calls; then set
# `PLAYER_CORS_ORIGINS` on core to include every player origin (e.g. http://localhost:5174,5175).
# VITE_PLAYER_API_ORIGIN=https://api.example.com
#
# Bonus card images: staff uploads are stored as /v1/uploads/... . For production split hostings, set
# API_PUBLIC_BASE on the core API (see services/core/.env.example) so /v1/rewards/hub returns absolute
# image URLs; you can still set VITE_PLAYER_API_ORIGIN as a fallback for the same effect on relative paths.

# Same-site cookie auth: enable on core (PLAYER_COOKIE_AUTH) and set:
# VITE_PLAYER_CREDENTIALS=1
# (JWTs are not written to localStorage; leftover keys are cleared on load; session uses httpOnly cookies + CSRF double-submit.)
# When core sets PLAYER_COOKIE_OMIT_JSON_TOKENS=true, login/refresh omit tokens in JSON — keep VITE_PLAYER_CREDENTIALS=1.

# VITE_TURNSTILE_SITE_KEY=

# Optional footer links on profile
# VITE_SUPPORT_URL=https://example.com/help
# VITE_RG_URL=https://example.com/responsible-gambling

# Region / maintenance shells (optional): shown on gate screens
# VITE_PUBLIC_SUPPORT_EMAIL=support@vybebet.com
# VITE_BRAND_FACEBOOK_URL=
# VITE_BRAND_X_URL=
# VITE_BRAND_INSTAGRAM_URL=
# VITE_BRAND_LINKEDIN_URL=
# VITE_BRAND_TELEGRAM_URL=

# Optional: publisher / B2B affiliate program (opens from Refer & Earn modal).
# When unset, "Become a partner" and "Join affiliate program" use the same-origin URL `/affiliate` (add a page or HTTP redirect there, or set this for an external portal).
# VITE_AFFILIATE_PROGRAM_URL=https://example.com/affiliates

# Admin console SPA origin (separate deploy). Used by optional cross-app helpers if enabled.
# VITE_ADMIN_APP_ORIGIN=http://localhost:5173

# --- Pigmo-style icon assets (optional) ---
# Shell icons: JSON map of slot → absolute URL. Slots: search, menu, message, bell, user, wallet.
# Capture URLs from DevTools → Network on https://pigmo.com/ (imagedelivery.net, .svg, .webp).
# Example (single line, minified):
# VITE_PIGMO_SHELL_ICONS={"search":"https://…/public","bell":"https://…/public"}
# VITE_PIGMO_SHELL_ICONS=
#
# Or point at a CF Images folder where you uploaded Pigmo glyphs as `{slot}.webp`:
# VITE_PIGMO_SHELL_ICON_BASE=https://imagedelivery.net/ACCOUNT_HASH/your-folder-id
#
# Use Pigmo Cloudflare “futures-icons” for BTC/ETH/SOL/DOGE wallet logos (see src/lib/pigmoIconAssets.ts).
# VITE_PIGMO_FUTURES_CRYPTO_ICONS=1
#
# Optional: map aggregator provider_system codes → Pigmo CF logo basename (slug). JSON object.
# Example: VITE_PROVIDER_LOGO_SLUGS_JSON={"qr":"quickspin","ae":"avatarux"}
# VITE_PROVIDER_LOGO_SLUGS_JSON=

# --- Fingerprint Pro (legacy / off by default). SDK does not load unless all of:
# VITE_FINGERPRINT_ENABLED=1
# VITE_FINGERPRINT_PUBLIC_KEY=   (Dashboard → API keys → Public — never commit production keys)
# VITE_FINGERPRINT_REGION=eu     (or us / ap — must match workspace; EU needs eu)
#
# Core: REQUIRE_FINGERPRINT_PLAYER_AUTH=true + FINGERPRINT_SECRET_API_KEY + FINGERPRINT_API_BASE_URL when re-enabling.
# In Fingerprint → Security, allow your exact player origin or the agent can be blocked.
#
# VITE_FINGERPRINT_REGION only selects Fingerprint data region; it does not set the game API base.
# Production catalog/login still need VITE_PLAYER_API_ORIGIN (or <meta name="player-api-origin">) or /v1/games
# is requested from the static host and returns empty rows.

# --- Oddin.gg esports (Bifrost iframe) — public config only; brand token is safe for the client.
# Oddin supplies brand token + iframe script/base URLs after onboarding — see docs/oddin-iframe-integration.md
#
# **Localhost:** If the iframe works on Vercel but not on http://localhost:5174, you usually need either (1) the full
# block below in THIS file, or (2) ODDIN_ENABLED + ODDIN_BRAND_TOKEN + ODDIN_PUBLIC_* on **local** core so
# GET /v1/sportsbook/oddin/public-config works. If you use a **local** API (not DEV_API_PROXY to Render), **append**
# http://localhost:5174 to PLAYER_CORS_ORIGINS alongside your Vercel hosts — do not remove existing entries.
# **vite preview** uses production mode: put the same vars in `.env.production.local`, not only `.env.development`.
#
# **Either** set all VITE_* below **or** rely on core only: with ODDIN_ENABLED + ODDIN_BRAND_TOKEN + ODDIN_PUBLIC_* on the API,
# the player calls GET /v1/sportsbook/oddin/public-config and mounts Oddin's iframe without duplicating secrets on Vercel.
# Optional: VITE_ODDIN_ENABLED=1 alone triggers the client to wait for that endpoint; you can still set VITE_* to override or fill gaps.
# VITE_ODDIN_ENABLED=1
# VITE_ODDIN_ENV=integration
# VITE_ODDIN_BRAND_TOKEN=
# VITE_ODDIN_BASE_URL=https://bifrost.integration.oddin.gg
# VITE_ODDIN_SCRIPT_URL=https://bifrost.integration.oddin.gg/script.js
# VITE_ODDIN_THEME=
# VITE_ODDIN_DEFAULT_LANGUAGE=en
# VITE_ODDIN_DEFAULT_CURRENCY=USD
# VITE_ODDIN_DARK_MODE=true
# Oddin support: bisection without token — append ?oddin_guest=1 to /esports. Allowed in `vite dev` always; for
# `vite preview` / staging builds set: VITE_ODDIN_ALLOW_GUEST_QUERY=1
# VITE_ODDIN_ALLOW_GUEST_QUERY=1
# Production: VITE_ODDIN_ENV=production, VITE_ODDIN_BASE_URL=https://bifrost.oddin.gg, VITE_ODDIN_SCRIPT_URL=https://bifrost.oddin.gg/script.js
# Core must set ODDIN_ENABLED=1 and issue tokens; see services/core/.env.example.
